This article is about an executive order issued by President Barack Obama in 2012. The order aims to improve visa and foreign visitor processing and travel promotion in the United States in order to create jobs and spur economic growth. The travel and tourism industry is identified as one of the nation's leading service sectors and sources of exports. The order establishes goals for increasing nonimmigrant visa processing capacity in China and Brazil, ensuring timely visa interviews for applicants, expanding the Visa Waiver Program, and implementing expedited travel programs. It also establishes a Task Force on Travel and Competitiveness to develop a National Travel and Tourism Strategy. The strategy aims to increase the United States' market share of worldwide travel and promote domestic and international travel opportunities throughout the country. The order is to be implemented consistent with applicable law and subject to the availability of appropriations.